<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Red Wings Re-Acquire Todd Gill  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   DETROIT (AP) -- The Detroit Red Wings, looking for an experienced
defenseman, reacquired Todd Gill late Monday for minor league left
wing Philippe Audet.
</P>
<P>
   Gill, 35, had one goal and six assists in 41 games with the
Coyotes this season. He was a minus-10.
</P>
<P>
   ''It was a good opportunity to take Todd and trade him back to
Detroit,'' said Coyotes general manager Bobby Smith. ''I think he's
happy with the move. He wasn't playing a lot and he wasn't happy
with his ice time.''
</P>
<P>
   Gill signed with the Coyotes as a free agent before the start of
the season after playing for the Wings the last half of the 1998-99
season after being waived by St. Louis.
</P>
<P>
   The defenseman, who missed 24 games with a broken forearm, had
two goals and two assists in 23 games for Detroit last season.
</P>
<P>
   Audet, the Wings' second-round choice in the 1995 draft, was the
third-leading scorer for the Cincinnati Cyclones of the IHL with 19
goals and 22 assists. He also had 115 penalty minutes.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
