<SUBHEAD>
Bush, Gore Campaigns Shifting South
</SUBHEAD>
<P>
   AUSTIN, Texas (AP) -- George W. Bush and Al Gore basked in the glory of their
home states Tuesday as voters in Texas, Tennessee and four other Southern states
went to the polls for primary elections. Bush, the Texas governor, was tending
to state business after voting last week by absentee ballot. Gore, the vice
president, was headed back to Florida after voting at home in Tennessee. A day
earlier, both men sought to cast themselves as reformers.
</P>
<SUBHEAD>
U.S. To Release China Trade Text
</SUBHEAD>
<P>
   WASHINGTON (AP) -- Supporters of legislation to implement an accord opening
trade barriers between China and the United States are hoping the law will be
easier to sell with release of the text of the landmark agreement.
Administration officials said the document's text would be sent Tuesday to each
member of Congress and released to the news media. Commerce Secretary William
Daley, the administration's point man on the lobbying effort, said Monday that
once people examine the fine print, ''They will see a very positive deal'' for
American exporters.
