Delta Plane Makes Emergency Landing
</SUBHEAD>
<P>
   SAN FRANCISCO (AP) -- A Delta Air Lines flight bound from San Francisco to
Salt Lake City made an emergency landing Monday evening after experiencing
problems with its landing gear, according to an airport spokeswoman. The Boeing
727-200 landed without any injuries to the 77 passengers, although the pilots
could not use their right landing gear, said airport spokeswoman Kim Dickie.
Emergency crews were waiting for the flight. The pilot informed the passengers
of the landing gear problems soon after takeoff. The plane then circled the
airport for an hour and dumped fuel.
</P>
