<HEADLINE> Nasdaq Jumps 90; Dow Gains 21  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- The Dow Jones industrial average is up 21 points
in today's early going. Advancing and declining issues are evenly
split on the New York Stock Exchange.
</P>
<P>
   The Nasdaq Composite Index is ahead 90 points and the Standard &AMP;
Poor's 500 Stock Index is up six points.
</P>
<P>
   Wall Street appears to be in modest recovery mode today after a
scary start to yesterday's session.
</P>
<P>
   Both the Dow and the Nasdaq began the day with drops of about
200 points.
</P>
<P>
   The Dow recovered to finish slightly higher but the Nasdaq still
posted its fourth-worst point drop ever.
</P>
<P>
   Market watchers say it appears the Dow is in the process of
forming a bottom from which it can move higher.
</P>
<P>
   The Nasdaq, having soared so high recently, may have more rough
days ahead.
</P>
<P>
   A report this morning showed retail sales at a
stronger-than-expected pace last month.
</P>
<P>
   Bond prices are steady.
</P>
<P>
   European markets are narrowly higher.
</P>
