<P>
   LOS ANGELES (AP) -- ''Law &AMP; Order'' star Angie Harmon said
''yes'' to a surprise marriage proposal from her football
player-boyfriend, Jason Sehorn, on ''The Tonight Show.''
</P>
<P>
   While interviewing the former model Monday, host Jay Leno asked
if she was dating someone special. Harmon, 28, who plays a
hard-charging assistant district attorney on the NBC crime drama,
said she never talks publicly about her personal life.
</P>
<P>
   Then Leno called Sehorn's name, and the New York Giants
defensive back walked on stage, knelt down and proposed.
</P>
