<DATE_TIME> 2000-03-14 20:34 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Swedish Leader Doubles As Porn Star  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   STOCKHOLM, Sweden (AP)-- A leftist politician may face expulsion
from his party because of his side career acting in pornographic
movies, a party spokesman said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
   The local branch of the Leftist party, which has supports
feminist and anti-pornography views, was reacting to a report in
the daily newspaper Goteborg-Posten that councilor Goeran Eurenius,
47, had acted in 14 pornographic movies.
</P>
<P>
   The 47-year-old actor/politician said his leftist political
beliefs were intact and he had done nothing wrong.
</P>
<P>
   ''I want to work both with politics and pornography,'' Eurenius
said in a telephone interview.
</P>
<P>
   The party plans to discuss the future of Eurenius, who could be
expelled, party secretary Lars Ohly said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
   ''If the local branch decides to expel him, he can appeal to the
national party, which then has a final say,'' Ohly said.
</P>
<P>
   Eurenius, who was elected in 1998 for a four-year term, said the
party has known about his acting career for at least a year and he
has no plans to resign.
</P>
<P>
   ''No I am not planning to resign. If they expel me, I will
remain as an independent throughout the term,'' he said. ''I am
elected by the people. My leftist views are no different because of
this.''
</P>
<P>
   Eurenius is a local councilor in Haerryda, 310 miles southwest
of the capital, Stockholm.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER> AP-NY-03-14-00 2034 </TRAILER>
