<DATE_TIME> 2000-03-14 20:58 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Tokyo Stocks Fall  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   TOKYO (AP) -- Japanese stocks fell early Wednesday following
sharp drops on Wall Street. The dollar was lower against the yen.
</P>
<P>
   The benchmark 225-issue Nikkei Stock Average shed 156.41 points,
or 0.82 percent, to 18,985.43 in the first 30 minutes of trading.
On Tuesday, the average fell 48.09 points, or 0.25 percent.
</P>
<P>
   The dollar bought 105.12 yen, down 0.02 yen from late Tuesday in
Tokyo and also below its late New York level of 105.05 yen.
</P>
<P>
   On the stock market, high-priced high technology issues and
telecommunication stocks were leading the market down, dampened by
the Nasdaq composite index's plunge Tuesday on Wall Street.
</P>
<P>
   In New York, the Nasdaq fell 200.61, or 4.1 percent, to close at
4,706.63, its second-worst point drop in history. The Dow Jones
industrial average closed down 135.89, to 9,811.24.
</P>
<P>
   ''The market looks set to test the downside,'' said Hiroichi
Nishi, an equities manager at Nikko Securities.
</P>
<P>
   The broader Tokyo Stock Price Index of all issues listed on the
first section was down 1.87 points, or 0.12 percent, to 1,580.10.
The TOPIX closed up 23.82 points, or 1.5 percent, the day before.
</P>
<P>
   In currency dealings, the dollar's slip came after major
Japanese banks sold the greenback and amid some profit-taking in
early Tokyo trading.
</P>
<P>
   The yen's strength in recent days has been based on some
positive factors such as rising machine orders and capital
expenditure, despite a 1.4 percent contraction in gross domestic
product in the October-December quarter.
</P>
<P>
   GDP is a major indicator representing the total goods and
services produced in a given period.
</P>
<P>
   In other currencies, the euro was traded at 101.70 yen, up from
101.22 yen late Tuesday in Tokyo.
</P>
<P>
   The yield on the benchmark 10-year Japanese government bond was
unquoted in early trading. On Tuesday, it settled at 1.7950 percent
and its price stood at 100.04.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
