<HEADLINE> Accused Killer Urged To Surrender  </HEADLINE>
By ALEX DOMINGUEZ, Associated Press Writer
<TEXT>
<P>
   BOWLEYS QUARTERS, Md. (AP) -- The girlfriend of a man accused of
kidnapping her and killing four people urged him Tuesday to
surrender and end a weeklong manhunt.
</P>
<P>
   Joseph Palczynksi's girlfriend, Tracy Whitehead, escaped from
him March 8, a day after she was kidnapped, according to police.
</P>
<P>
   ''The other night in the woods you told me how you loved me and
wanted to marry me,'' Whitehead said in a handwritten note signed
with a heart. ''If you really love me, show me by turning yourself
in.
</P>
<P>
   ''I know you have a lot of good in you, so let's bring this to
an end. I know you can do it.''
</P>
<P>
   Police are hoping Palczynksi will hear her plea via a
battery-operated television investigators believe he bought, along
with outdoor gear, last week.
</P>
<P>
   Palczynski has been the subject of an around-the-clock manhunt
since Whitehead was kidnapped at gunpoint from a co-worker's
apartment. She had moved in with Gloria Jean Shenk and her husband,
George, after Palczynski beat her while she tried to move out of
the apartment they shared, she told police.
</P>
<P>
   Police say he bought a shotgun and rifle and, on March 7,
kidnapped Whitehead, fatally shooting the Shenks and David Meyers,
a neighbor who tried to help.
</P>
<P>
   The next day, Jennifer Lynn McDonel, 36, was on her way to
church services with her husband when she was fatally struck by a
stray bullet as Palczynski carjacked another vehicle, according to
police.
</P>
<P>
   A longtime friend of Palczynski, attorney David Henniger, also
read a statement that was broadcast by TV stations.
</P>
<P>
   ''We need the killing to cease; don't do anything to make things
worse,'' Henniger said. ''I can do a lot more for you, the sooner
you call.''
</P>
</TEXT>
