<HEADLINE> Magic 107, Wizards 98  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   ORLANDO, Fla. (AP) -- Monty Williams scored 19 points, and Ron
Mercer added 18 in his return from a five-game absence Tuesday
night as the Orlando Magic beat the Washington Wizards 107-98.
</P>
<P>
   Five players scored in double figures for Orlando, which has won
four of five games.
</P>
<P>
   The Magic used a 15-3 run to end the third quarter and build an
83-66 lead. Washington didn't get back to within 10 points until
the final minute of the game.
</P>
<P>
   Mercer had six points in the key run. He missed four games with
an ankle sprain and then was suspended by the NBA for a game for
fighting with former Denver Nuggets teammate George McCloud after
the teams played Saturday.
</P>
<P>
   Washington reserve Lamond Murray had a game-high 26 points,
while Mitch Richmond added 16 for the Wizards, who have now lost
three straight.
</P>
<P>
   Bolstered by the play of Williams, a reserve who had 13 points
in the opening 24 minutes, the Magic surged to a 62-55 halftime
lead.
Notes: Don Reid, a Georgetown University product recently cut by
Detroit, made a strong debut with Washington, scoring 12 points and
grabbing eight rebounds. ... Washington's substitutes outscored its
starters 45-43. ... The Wizards outrebounded the Magic 37-31. ...
Washington never led after the 5:16 mark of the first quarter. The
Magic led by as many as 13 points. ...
</P>
