Tokyo Stocks Fall
</SUBHEAD>
<P>
   TOKYO (AP) -- Japanese stocks fell Wednesday following sharp drops on Wall
Street. The Nikkei Stock Average shed 1230.79 points to 18,911.05 in early
trading. In New York, the Nasdaq fell 200.61, or 4.1 percent, to close at
4,706.63, its second-worst point drop in history. The Dow Jones industrial
average closed down 135.89, to 9,811.24.
</P>
